-{"id":"brenner_bot-tyyh","title":"Add demo mode handling to session sub-pages","description":"# Task: Graceful Demo Mode for Session Sub-Pages

## Context
Parent feature: Demo Sessions Page (brenner_bot-0y2e)
DEPENDS ON: Demo fixture data task (brenner_bot-tdvc)

## CRITICAL PROBLEM DISCOVERED
Multiple session sub-pages have `isLabModeEnabled()` checks and will show 'Lab Mode Locked' when accessed with demo session IDs:

| Page | Lab Mode Check Line |
|------|---------------------|
| /sessions/[threadId]/evidence/page.tsx | Line 414 |
| /sessions/[threadId]/test-queue/page.tsx | (likely similar) |
| /sessions/[threadId]/hypothesis/page.tsx | (likely similar) |
| /sessions/[threadId]/operators/page.tsx | (likely similar) |
| /sessions/[threadId]/brief/page.tsx | (likely similar) |
| /sessions/[threadId]/agents/page.tsx | (likely similar) |
| /sessions/new/page.tsx | Line 242 |

When a user clicks 'Evidence Pack' on a demo session detail page, they navigate to `/sessions/demo-xxx/evidence` and see... 'Lab Mode Locked'. This is jarring and breaks the demo experience.

## Solution: Graceful Degradation Pattern
Instead of full demo mode support (which would require fixtures for each sub-feature), implement a consistent 'Demo Preview' pattern:

### 1. Create shared utility
```typescript
// src/lib/demo-mode.ts

import { isDemoSession } from '@/lib/fixtures/demo-sessions';

export interface DemoPreviewProps {
  threadId: string;
  featureName: string;
  featureDescription: string;
}

/** Check if current page should show demo preview mode */
export function shouldShowDemoPreview(threadId: string): boolean {
  return isDemoSession(threadId);
}
```

### 2. Create DemoFeaturePreview component
```typescript
// src/components/sessions/DemoFeaturePreview.tsx

import Link from 'next/link';
import { FlaskConical, ArrowLeft, BookOpen } from 'lucide-react';

interface Props {
  threadId: string;
  featureName: string;
  featureDescription: string;
  learnMoreLink?: string;
}

export function DemoFeaturePreview({ 
  threadId, 
  featureName, 
  featureDescription,
  learnMoreLink = '/tutorial/quick-start'
}: Props) {
  return (
    <div className="max-w-2xl mx-auto space-y-6 animate-fade-in-up">
      {/* Demo Banner */}
      <div className="rounded-xl border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-950/20 p-6">
        <div className="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div className="flex items-center justify-center size-12 rounded-xl bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900/30 text-amber-600">
            <FlaskConical className="size-6" />
          </div>
          <div className="space-y-3">
            <h1 className="text-xl font-bold text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-100">
              {featureName} — Demo Preview
            </h1>
            <p className="text-sm text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">
              {featureDescription}
            </p>
            <p className="text-sm text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">
              This feature is available when running BrennerBot locally with Lab Mode enabled.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Navigation */}
      <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <Link
          href={`/sessions/${threadId}`}
          className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card text-sm font-medium hover:bg-muted/50"
        >
          <ArrowLeft className="size-4" />
          Back to Demo Session
        </Link>
        <Link
          href={learnMoreLink}
          className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-primary text-primary-foreground text-sm font-medium"
        >
          <BookOpen className="size-4" />
          Learn How to Set Up
        </Link>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 3. Update each sub-page
Add demo check BEFORE the lab mode check:

```typescript
// In each sub-page (evidence, test-queue, etc.)

import { isDemoSession } from '@/lib/fixtures/demo-sessions';
import { DemoFeaturePreview } from '@/components/sessions/DemoFeaturePreview';

export default async function EvidencePackPage({ params }) {
  const { threadId } = await params;

  // Handle demo sessions FIRST
  if (isDemoSession(threadId)) {
    return (
      <DemoFeaturePreview
        threadId={threadId}
        featureName="Evidence Pack"
        featureDescription="The Evidence Pack collects external papers, datasets, and experiment results that support or refute your hypotheses. Link evidence directly to specific claims for transparent reasoning."
      />
    );
  }

  // Then do normal lab mode check
  if (!isLabModeEnabled()) {
    return <LockedState reason="..." />;
  }

  // ... rest of the page
}
```

