 {"id":"brenner_bot-tzla","title":"Fix operator symbol drift + duplicated phase labels","description":"# Fix operator symbol drift + duplicated phase labels

## Symptoms
- Operator phases show duplicated symbols in some UI (e.g. badge renders `getPhaseSymbol()` plus `getPhaseName()` which already includes `(symbol)`).
- Local session/operator pages still show legacy operator symbols (Σ/⊘/⟳/⊙) instead of the canonical symbols in `specs/operator_library_v0.1.md` (⊘/✂/⟂/⊞).

## Fix
- Make `getPhaseName()` return plain names (no embedded symbols).
- Render operator symbols via `getPhaseSymbol()` where needed, conditionally (avoid empty symbol spans).
- Update local session hub + operators workspace to use canonical symbols.

## Files
- `apps/web/src/lib/brenner-loop/session-machine.ts`
- `apps/web/src/components/brenner-loop/SessionCard.tsx`
